   By PHILIP STEPHENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
DOWNING Street sought yesterday to dispel reports that Mr John Major was at
odds with Mr Norman Lamont over the need for tax increases in the March
Budget, Philip Stephens writes.
But the prime minister's aides did nothing to damp speculation that Mr Major
intends to take a leading role in deciding the shape of the eventual
