<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JAN 93 / Newcastle council to cut 480 jobs
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NEWCASTLE upon Tyne Council's controlling Labour group announced yesterday
that the council will have to shed 400 full and part-time jobs as part of a
Pounds 7.9m cuts package for 1993-94.
The group expects to make cuts totalling Pounds 20m in the coming three
financial years to keep within government spending targets, which have
pegged its 1993-94 budget at Pounds 222.5m.
