work with the organisation as it had not stopped political violence, writes
Victor Mallet in Bangkok.
In a weekend statement, Prince Sihanouk also said he had called a meeting of
Cambodia's Supreme National Council - which includes the four main political
factions - at his residence in Beijing on January 28.
His climbdown followed two hours of talks in Beijing on Friday with Mr
Yasushi Akashi, head of the UN transitional authority in Cambodia.
